text: Ina seemed super comfortable to me even in older collabs if they were all having fun together. I'm an introvert but when I'm talking to close friends or acquaintances I admire I can just go on forever. I think it's because I know the people and trust them. If I'm talking by myself like to random people or streaming to people that I have no clue who they are, it's like "what do they think of me? am i gonna say something that makes them think less of me?" Similarly I think that's how Gura feels about streaming to members vs public, she's straight up said she feels more relaxed doing member streams.
author: @Cat-Daddy

text: ¬†@Cat-Daddy¬† I mean don't get me wrong, she was never UNcomfortable during those collabs. She was usually the one dying of laughter after all. I've gone back to some of her older streams lately, and even her solo streams had a bit of a different feel to them at the time. Though to be fair, that goes for all of Holomyth. It'll be interesting to see how far they've come in about a year from now. Especially since they won't be the only ones in the EN group by then. (Well, only official ones.
